name: unduplicated
content:
Add to word list
Add to word list
Something that is unduplicated has not been done or experienced by anyone or anything else: The improvement in performance was unduplicated by any school in Scotland. At its core, the event is about creating unduplicated experiences.
only counted once: The unduplicated head count takes into account students who may be enrolled in classes on multiple campuses. These sites have an unduplicated audience of more than 140 million unique visitors.
More examplesFewer examplesThey are still building curriculum, creating what they say is an unduplicated early direction in health care education.That figure is unduplicated, meaning there is no double-counting of those who read the paper in print and online.
